history.content:
If there are no reserved seats during adjustment, seats freed by someone dropping goes to everyone (top of the WL gets in first whether you had reserved seats or not since there are no reserved seats during adjustment). This have been the case for CS classes.

Now if there are reserved seats during adjustment (typically in stats or ugba courses this is their policy) then freed seat would only go to those who have reserved seats.

For example, I'm like 120 on waitlist for 61c. However, when I checked on enrollment day, I think there were 20 reserved seats for undeclared ahead of me.

For example, the waitlist had 120 people with 1 reserved seat left for undeclared majors. I signed up on spot 140 (after that reserved seat was taken) and I am undeclared.

If people drop after adjustment period, do those seats go towards the reserved seating I mentioned or does it go to everyone. Thank you
history.subject: When adjustment period begins, do seats that people drop go into reserved seating or not?
